metadata.name: Thor
metadata.description: Thor is a deity in Norse mythology who is associated with thunder and lightning. He is often depicted as a powerful, muscular man with a hammer, and is associated with the element of fire and the destructive aspects of life. In Norse mythology, Thor is revered as the god of thunder and was believed to have the power to control the forces of nature. He was also associated with war and was believed to have the power to inspire courage and ferocity in battle. Thor was widely worshipped throughout the Norse-speaking world and was considered to be an important deity in Norse religion.
